{"metadata":{"kernelspec":{"display_name":"Python 3","language":"python","name":"python3"},"language_info":{"name":"python","version":"3.12.0"},"kaggle":{"accelerator":"nvidiaTeslaT4","dataSources":[{"sourceType":"competition","sourceId":138527,"databundleVersionId":16728716}],"dockerImageVersionId":31329,"isInternetEnabled":false,"language":"python","sourceType":"notebook","isGpuEnabled":true}},"nbformat_minor":4,"nbformat":4,"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# Plant Leaves Super-Resolution Challenge\n## Conditional GAN (cGAN) for 4x Super-Resolution\n\n**Task:** Reconstruct high-resolution 128x128 images from degraded 32x32 low-resolution inputs.  \n**Metric:** Mean Absolute Error (MAE) — lower is better.  \n**Baseline:** 17.3529644  \n**Architecture:** Conditional GAN with RCAB Generator and PatchGAN-style Discriminator","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 1. Imports and Setup","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"import os, random\nimport numpy as np\nimport pandas as pd\nfrom PIL import Image\nfrom tqdm.notebook import tqdm\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n\nimport torch\nimport torch.nn as nn\nimport torch.optim as optim\nfrom torch.utils.data import Dataset, DataLoader\nimport torchvision.transforms as transforms\nimport torchvision.transforms.functional as TF\nimport torchvision.models as models\n\nprint(f\"PyTorch : {torch.__version__}\")\nprint(f\"CUDA    : {torch.cuda.is_available()}\")\nif torch.cuda.is_available():\n    print(f\"GPU     : {torch.cuda.get_device_name(0)}\")","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 2. Configuration","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"SEED = 42\nrandom.seed(SEED); np.random.seed(SEED); torch.manual_seed(SEED)\nDEVICE = torch.device(\"cuda\" if torch.cuda.is_available() else \"cpu\")\nprint(f\"Device : {DEVICE}\")\n\nDATA_ROOT    = \"/kaggle/input/competitions/plant-leaves-super-resolution-challenge\"\nTRAIN_HR_DIR = os.path.join(DATA_ROOT, \"train_High_Resolution\")\nTRAIN_LR_DIR = os.path.join(DATA_ROOT, \"train_Low_Resolution\")\nTEST_LR_DIR  = os.path.join(DATA_ROOT, \"test_Low_Resolution\")\nVGG_WEIGHTS  = os.path.join(DATA_ROOT, \"vgg19_weights.pth\")\nOUTPUT_DIR   = \"/kaggle/working\"\n\nBATCH_SIZE = 8\nNUM_EPOCHS = 150\nLR_INIT    = 2e-4\nLAMBDA_PERC = 0.005\nLAMBDA_GAN  = 0.001\n\nprint(f\"Train HR : {len(os.listdir(TRAIN_HR_DIR))} images\")\nprint(f\"Train LR : {len(os.listdir(TRAIN_LR_DIR))} images\")\nprint(f\"Test LR  : {len(os.listdir(TEST_LR_DIR))} images\")\nprint(f\"VGG19    : {'EXISTS' if os.path.exists(VGG_WEIGHTS) else 'NOT FOUND'}\")","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 3. Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)\n\n### 3.1 Dataset Overview","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"train_hr_files = sorted(os.listdir(TRAIN_HR_DIR))\ntrain_lr_files = sorted(os.listdir(TRAIN_LR_DIR))\ntest_lr_files  = sorted(os.listdir(TEST_LR_DIR))\n\nprint(\"-\" * 50)\nprint(\"DATASET OVERVIEW\")\nprint(\"-\" * 50)\nprint(f\"Training pairs : {len(train_hr_files)}\")\nprint(f\"Test images    : {len(test_lr_files)}\")\n\nsample_hr = Image.open(os.path.join(TRAIN_HR_DIR, train_hr_files[0]))\nsample_lr = Image.open(os.path.join(TRAIN_LR_DIR, train_lr_files[0]))\nprint(f\"HR image size  : {sample_hr.size} | Mode: {sample_hr.mode}\")\nprint(f\"LR image size  : {sample_lr.size} | Mode: {sample_lr.mode}\")\nprint(f\"Scale factor   : {sample_hr.size[0] // sample_lr.size[0]}x\")","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### 3.2 Sample LR vs HR Image Pairs","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"fig, axes = plt.subplots(3, 4, figsize=(16, 10))\nfig.suptitle(\"Sample LR Input vs HR Ground Truth vs Bicubic Baseline\",\n             fontsize=13, fontweight='bold')\n\nindices = random.sample(range(len(train_hr_files)), 4)\nfor col, idx in enumerate(indices):\n    lr_img = Image.open(os.path.join(TRAIN_LR_DIR, train_lr_files[idx]))\n    hr_img = Image.open(os.path.join(TRAIN_HR_DIR, train_hr_files[idx]))\n    lr_up  = lr_img.resize((128, 128), Image.BICUBIC)\n\n    axes[0, col].imshow(lr_img)\n    axes[0, col].set_title(\"LR 32x32\", fontsize=9)\n    axes[0, col].axis(\"off\")\n\n    axes[1, col].imshow(hr_img)\n    axes[1, col].set_title(\"HR 128x128 (Ground Truth)\", fontsize=9)\n    axes[1, col].axis(\"off\")\n\n    axes[2, col].imshow(lr_up)\n    axes[2, col].set_title(\"Bicubic x4\", fontsize=9)\n    axes[2, col].axis(\"off\")\n\naxes[0, 0].set_ylabel(\"LR Input\", fontsize=10, fontweight='bold')\naxes[1, 0].set_ylabel(\"Ground Truth\", fontsize=10, fontweight='bold')\naxes[2, 0].set_ylabel(\"Bicubic Baseline\", fontsize=10, fontweight='bold')\n\nplt.tight_layout()\nplt.savefig(os.path.join(OUTPUT_DIR, \"eda_sample_pairs.png\"), dpi=120)\nplt.show()","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### 3.3 Pixel Statistics","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"print(\"Computing pixel statistics on 50 random samples...\")\nhr_pixels, lr_pixels = [], []\nsample_idx = random.sample(range(len(train_hr_files)), 50)\n\nfor i in sample_idx:\n    hr = np.array(Image.open(os.path.join(TRAIN_HR_DIR, train_hr_files[i])))\n    lr = np.array(Image.open(os.path.join(TRAIN_LR_DIR, train_lr_files[i])))\n    hr_pixels.append(hr.flatten())\n    lr_pixels.append(lr.flatten())\n\nhr_pixels = np.concatenate(hr_pixels)\nlr_pixels = np.concatenate(lr_pixels)\n\nprint(f\"HR - Mean: {hr_pixels.mean():.2f} | Std: {hr_pixels.std():.2f} | Range: [{hr_pixels.min()}, {hr_pixels.max()}]\")\nprint(f\"LR - Mean: {lr_pixels.mean():.2f} | Std: {lr_pixels.std():.2f} | Range: [{lr_pixels.min()}, {lr_pixels.max()}]\")\n\nfig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 4))\nfig.suptitle(\"Pixel Distribution Analysis\", fontsize=13, fontweight='bold')\n\naxes[0].hist(hr_pixels, bins=50, color='seagreen', alpha=0.7, label='HR')\naxes[0].hist(lr_pixels, bins=50, color='royalblue', alpha=0.7, label='LR')\naxes[0].set_title(\"Pixel Value Distribution\")\naxes[0].set_xlabel(\"Pixel Value\")\naxes[0].set_ylabel(\"Frequency\")\naxes[0].legend()\n\nhr_arr = np.array([np.array(Image.open(os.path.join(TRAIN_HR_DIR, train_hr_files[i])))\n                   for i in sample_idx[:20]])\nchannel_means = hr_arr.mean(axis=(0, 1, 2))\naxes[1].bar(['Red', 'Green', 'Blue'], channel_means,\n            color=['tomato', 'seagreen', 'royalblue'])\naxes[1].set_title(\"HR Mean Pixel Value per Channel\")\naxes[1].set_ylabel(\"Mean Pixel Value\")\nfor i, v in enumerate(channel_means):\n    axes[1].text(i, v + 1, f\"{v:.1f}\", ha='center', fontweight='bold')\n\nplt.tight_layout()\nplt.savefig(os.path.join(OUTPUT_DIR, \"eda_pixel_stats.png\"), dpi=120)\nplt.show()","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### 3.4 Bicubic Baseline MAE","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"print(\"Computing bicubic baseline MAE...\")\nbicubic_maes = []\nfor i in sample_idx[:30]:\n    hr  = np.array(Image.open(os.path.join(TRAIN_HR_DIR, train_hr_files[i]))).astype(float)\n    lr  = Image.open(os.path.join(TRAIN_LR_DIR, train_lr_files[i]))\n    bic = np.array(lr.resize((128, 128), Image.BICUBIC)).astype(float)\n    bicubic_maes.append(np.mean(np.abs(hr - bic)))\n\nprint(f\"Bicubic baseline MAE : {np.mean(bicubic_maes):.4f}\")\nprint(f\"Competition baseline : 17.3529\")\nprint(f\"Our target           : below 16.0\")\n\nfig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(7, 4))\nfig.suptitle(\"MAE Comparison\", fontsize=13, fontweight='bold')\nbars = ax.bar(\n    [\"Bicubic\\nBaseline\", \"Competition\\nBaseline\", \"Our Target\"],\n    [np.mean(bicubic_maes), 17.3529, 16.0],\n    color=[\"royalblue\", \"tomato\", \"seagreen\"],\n    width=0.5\n)\nax.set_ylabel(\"MAE (lower is better)\")\nax.axhline(17.3529, color='red', linestyle='--', alpha=0.4)\nfor bar, val in zip(bars, [np.mean(bicubic_maes), 17.3529, 16.0]):\n    ax.text(bar.get_x() + bar.get_width()/2, val + 0.1,\n            f\"{val:.2f}\", ha='center', fontweight='bold')\nplt.tight_layout()\nplt.savefig(os.path.join(OUTPUT_DIR, \"eda_baselines.png\"), dpi=120)\nplt.show()","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### 3.5 Test Set Overview","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"print(f\"Test images     : {len(test_lr_files)}\")\nprint(f\"Test image size : {Image.open(os.path.join(TEST_LR_DIR, test_lr_files[0])).size}\")\n\nfig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 6, figsize=(18, 6))\nfig.suptitle(\"Sample Test Images (LR Input to be Super-Resolved)\",\n             fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')\n\nfor i in range(6):\n    img = Image.open(os.path.join(TEST_LR_DIR, test_lr_files[i]))\n    axes[0, i].imshow(img)\n    axes[0, i].set_title(test_lr_files[i][:18], fontsize=7)\n    axes[0, i].axis(\"off\")\n\n    img_up = img.resize((128, 128), Image.BICUBIC)\n    axes[1, i].imshow(img_up)\n    axes[1, i].set_title(\"Bicubic x4\", fontsize=7)\n    axes[1, i].axis(\"off\")\n\naxes[0, 0].set_ylabel(\"LR 32x32\", fontsize=9, fontweight='bold')\naxes[1, 0].set_ylabel(\"Bicubic 128x128\", fontsize=9, fontweight='bold')\n\nplt.tight_layout()\nplt.savefig(os.path.join(OUTPUT_DIR, \"eda_test_overview.png\"), dpi=120)\nplt.show()","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 4. Dataset Class","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"class SRDataset(Dataset):\n    def __init__(self, lr_dir, hr_dir=None, augment=False):\n        self.lr_dir    = lr_dir\n        self.hr_dir    = hr_dir\n        self.augment   = augment\n        self.lr_files  = sorted(os.listdir(lr_dir))\n        self.to_tensor = transforms.ToTensor()\n\n    def __len__(self): return len(self.lr_files)\n\n    def __getitem__(self, idx):\n        fname  = self.lr_files[idx]\n        lr_img = Image.open(os.path.join(self.lr_dir, fname)).convert(\"RGB\")\n\n        if self.hr_dir is not None:\n            hr_img = Image.open(os.path.join(self.hr_dir, fname)).convert(\"RGB\")\n            if self.augment:\n                if random.random() > 0.5:\n                    lr_img, hr_img = TF.hflip(lr_img), TF.hflip(hr_img)\n                if random.random() > 0.5:\n                    lr_img, hr_img = TF.vflip(lr_img), TF.vflip(hr_img)\n                angle = random.choice([0, 90, 180, 270])\n                if angle != 0:\n                    lr_img = TF.rotate(lr_img, angle)\n                    hr_img = TF.rotate(hr_img, angle)\n            return self.to_tensor(lr_img), self.to_tensor(hr_img), fname\n        return self.to_tensor(lr_img), fname\n\ntrain_ds     = SRDataset(TRAIN_LR_DIR, TRAIN_HR_DIR, augment=True)\ntrain_loader = DataLoader(train_ds, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=True, num_workers=2)\nprint(f\"Training samples  : {len(train_ds)}\")\nprint(f\"Batches per epoch : {len(train_loader)}\")","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 5. Model Architecture\n\nThe model is a Conditional GAN (cGAN). The Generator uses Residual Channel Attention Blocks (RCAB) with PixelShuffle upsampling. The Discriminator is conditioned on the bicubic-upscaled LR image concatenated with the SR or HR image. All weights are randomly initialized.\n\n### 5.1 Channel Attention Module","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"class ChannelAttention(nn.Module):\n    def __init__(self, channel, reduction=16):\n        super().__init__()\n        self.avg_pool = nn.AdaptiveAvgPool2d(1)\n        self.conv = nn.Sequential(\n            nn.Conv2d(channel, channel // reduction, 1, bias=False),\n            nn.ReLU(inplace=True),\n            nn.Conv2d(channel // reduction, channel, 1, bias=False),\n            nn.Sigmoid()\n        )\n    def forward(self, x):\n        return x * self.conv(self.avg_pool(x))\n\nprint(\"ChannelAttention defined.\")","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### 5.2 Residual Channel Attention Block (RCAB)","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"class RCAB(nn.Module):\n    def __init__(self, in_ch, res_scale=0.1):\n        super().__init__()\n        self.res_scale = res_scale\n        self.conv1 = nn.Conv2d(in_ch, in_ch, 3, padding=1)\n        self.relu  = nn.ReLU(inplace=True)\n        self.conv2 = nn.Conv2d(in_ch, in_ch, 3, padding=1)\n        self.ca    = ChannelAttention(in_ch)\n\n    def forward(self, x):\n        res = self.ca(self.conv2(self.relu(self.conv1(x))))\n        return x + (res * self.res_scale)\n\nprint(\"RCAB defined.\")","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### 5.3 Generator","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"class SRGenerator(nn.Module):\n    def __init__(self, F=96, num_rcab=16):\n        super().__init__()\n        self.conv_first = nn.Conv2d(3, F, 3, padding=1)\n        self.body       = nn.Sequential(*[RCAB(F, res_scale=0.1) for _ in range(num_rcab)])\n        self.conv_body  = nn.Conv2d(F, F, 3, padding=1)\n        self.upsample   = nn.Sequential(\n            nn.Conv2d(F, F * 4, 3, padding=1), nn.PixelShuffle(2), nn.ReLU(inplace=True),\n            nn.Conv2d(F, F * 4, 3, padding=1), nn.PixelShuffle(2), nn.ReLU(inplace=True),\n        )\n        self.conv_last  = nn.Conv2d(F, 3, 3, padding=1)\n        self.bicubic_up = nn.Upsample(scale_factor=4, mode='bicubic')\n\n    def forward(self, x):\n        bicubic = self.bicubic_up(x)\n        feat    = self.conv_first(x)\n        res     = self.conv_body(self.body(feat))\n        out     = self.conv_last(self.upsample(feat + res))\n        return torch.clamp(out + bicubic, 0.0, 1.0)\n\ngenerator = SRGenerator(F=96, num_rcab=16).to(DEVICE)\nprint(f\"Generator parameters : {sum(p.numel() for p in generator.parameters()):,}\")\n\nwith torch.no_grad():\n    dummy = torch.randn(1, 3, 32, 32).to(DEVICE)\n    out   = generator(dummy)\n    print(f\"Input  : {dummy.shape}\")\n    print(f\"Output : {out.shape}\")\n    print(f\"Output range : [{out.min():.3f}, {out.max():.3f}]\")","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### 5.4 Conditional Discriminator\n\nThe discriminator is conditioned on the bicubic-upscaled LR image. It receives a 6-channel input (3 channels from LR upscaled + 3 channels from SR or HR) and outputs a real/fake score.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"class Discriminator(nn.Module):\n    def __init__(self):\n        super().__init__()\n        def block(in_ch, out_ch, stride=1, bn=True):\n            layers = [nn.Conv2d(in_ch, out_ch, 3, stride=stride, padding=1, bias=not bn)]\n            if bn: layers.append(nn.BatchNorm2d(out_ch))\n            layers.append(nn.LeakyReLU(0.2, inplace=True))\n            return nn.Sequential(*layers)\n\n        # Input: 6 channels (LR bicubic upscaled + SR/HR concatenated)\n        self.net = nn.Sequential(\n            block(6,   64,  stride=1, bn=False),\n            block(64,  128, stride=2),\n            block(128, 256, stride=2),\n            block(256, 512, stride=2),\n            nn.AdaptiveAvgPool2d(1),\n            nn.Flatten(),\n            nn.Linear(512, 1),\n        )\n\n    def forward(self, lr_up, img):\n        # Conditional: discriminator sees LR context + SR or HR image\n        x = torch.cat([lr_up, img], dim=1)\n        return self.net(x)\n\ndiscriminator = Discriminator().to(DEVICE)\nprint(f\"Discriminator parameters : {sum(p.numel() for p in discriminator.parameters()):,}\")\n\n# Bicubic upsampler for conditioning\nbicubic_up = nn.Upsample(scale_factor=4, mode='bicubic').to(DEVICE)","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 6. Loss Functions and Optimizers","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Charbonnier Loss (smooth L1 variant, better than plain L1 for SR)\nclass CharbonnierLoss(nn.Module):\n    def __init__(self, eps=1e-3):\n        super().__init__()\n        self.eps = eps\n    def forward(self, x, y):\n        return torch.mean(torch.sqrt((x - y) ** 2 + self.eps ** 2))\n\n# Perceptual Loss using provided VGG19 weights (no internet required)\nclass OfflinePerceptualLoss(nn.Module):\n    def __init__(self):\n        super().__init__()\n        vgg = models.vgg19()\n        vgg.load_state_dict(torch.load(VGG_WEIGHTS, map_location=DEVICE))\n        self.vgg = vgg.features[:18].eval().to(DEVICE)\n        for p in self.vgg.parameters():\n            p.requires_grad = False\n        print(\"VGG19 loaded from local dataset file.\")\n\n    def forward(self, sr, hr):\n        return nn.functional.l1_loss(self.vgg(sr), self.vgg(hr))\n\ncriterion_charb = CharbonnierLoss().to(DEVICE)\ncriterion_perc  = OfflinePerceptualLoss()\ncriterion_gan   = nn.BCEWithLogitsLoss().to(DEVICE)\n\noptimizer_G = optim.AdamW(generator.parameters(),     lr=LR_INIT,       weight_decay=1e-4)\noptimizer_D = optim.AdamW(discriminator.parameters(), lr=LR_INIT * 0.1, weight_decay=1e-4)\n\nscheduler_G = optim.lr_scheduler.CosineAnnealingWarmRestarts(optimizer_G, T_0=50, T_mult=2)\nscheduler_D = optim.lr_scheduler.CosineAnnealingWarmRestarts(optimizer_D, T_0=50, T_mult=2)\n\nprint(f\"Loss G    : Charbonnier + Perceptual (w={LAMBDA_PERC}) + GAN (w={LAMBDA_GAN})\")\nprint(f\"Loss D    : BCEWithLogits\")\nprint(f\"Optimizer : AdamW  lr_G={LR_INIT}  lr_D={LR_INIT * 0.1}\")","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 7. Training","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"history   = {\"epoch\": [], \"loss_G\": [], \"loss_D\": [], \"lr\": []}\nbest_loss = float(\"inf\")\nckpt_path = os.path.join(OUTPUT_DIR, \"best_generator.pth\")\n\nprint(f\"Training cGAN for {NUM_EPOCHS} epochs on {DEVICE}\")\nprint(\"=\" * 65)\n\nfor epoch in range(1, NUM_EPOCHS + 1):\n    generator.train()\n    discriminator.train()\n    epoch_loss_G, epoch_loss_D, nb = 0.0, 0.0, 0\n\n    for lr_imgs, hr_imgs, _ in train_loader:\n        lr_imgs = lr_imgs.to(DEVICE)\n        hr_imgs = hr_imgs.to(DEVICE)\n        bs      = lr_imgs.size(0)\n\n        lr_up = bicubic_up(lr_imgs).clamp(0, 1)\n\n        real_labels = torch.ones (bs, 1).to(DEVICE)\n        fake_labels = torch.zeros(bs, 1).to(DEVICE)\n\n        # --- Train Generator ---\n        optimizer_G.zero_grad()\n        sr = generator(lr_imgs)\n\n        loss_charb = criterion_charb(sr, hr_imgs)\n        loss_perc  = criterion_perc(sr, hr_imgs)\n        fake_pred  = discriminator(lr_up, sr)\n        loss_adv   = criterion_gan(fake_pred, real_labels)\n        loss_G     = loss_charb + LAMBDA_PERC * loss_perc + LAMBDA_GAN * loss_adv\n\n        loss_G.backward()\n        torch.nn.utils.clip_grad_norm_(generator.parameters(), max_norm=1.0)\n        optimizer_G.step()\n\n        # --- Train Discriminator ---\n        optimizer_D.zero_grad()\n        real_pred = discriminator(lr_up, hr_imgs)\n        fake_pred = discriminator(lr_up, sr.detach())\n        loss_D    = (criterion_gan(real_pred, real_labels) +\n                     criterion_gan(fake_pred, fake_labels)) * 0.5\n\n        loss_D.backward()\n        optimizer_D.step()\n\n        epoch_loss_G += loss_charb.item()\n        epoch_loss_D += loss_D.item()\n        nb += 1\n\n    scheduler_G.step()\n    scheduler_D.step()\n\n    avg_G  = (epoch_loss_G / nb) * 255\n    avg_D  = epoch_loss_D / nb\n    cur_lr = optimizer_G.param_groups[0]['lr']\n\n    history[\"epoch\"].append(epoch)\n    history[\"loss_G\"].append(avg_G)\n    history[\"loss_D\"].append(avg_D)\n    history[\"lr\"].append(cur_lr)\n\n    saved = \"\"\n    if avg_G < best_loss:\n        best_loss = avg_G\n        torch.save(generator.state_dict(), ckpt_path)\n        saved = \"  saved\"\n\n    if epoch % 10 == 0 or epoch == 1:\n        print(f\"Ep {epoch:3d}/{NUM_EPOCHS} | \"\n              f\"G MAE: {avg_G:.2f} | \"\n              f\"D Loss: {avg_D:.4f} | \"\n              f\"LR: {cur_lr:.6f}{saved}\")\n\nprint(f\"\\nTraining complete. Best G MAE: {best_loss:.4f}\")","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 8. Training Curves","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(18, 4))\nfig.suptitle(\"Training History\", fontsize=13, fontweight='bold')\n\naxes[0].plot(history[\"epoch\"], history[\"loss_G\"], color=\"royalblue\")\naxes[0].axhline(17.35, color=\"red\",    linestyle=\"--\", label=\"Baseline 17.35\")\naxes[0].axhline(16.0,  color=\"orange\", linestyle=\"--\", label=\"Target 16.0\")\naxes[0].set_title(\"Generator MAE per Epoch\")\naxes[0].set_xlabel(\"Epoch\")\naxes[0].set_ylabel(\"MAE\")\naxes[0].legend()\n\naxes[1].plot(history[\"epoch\"], history[\"loss_D\"], color=\"tomato\")\naxes[1].set_title(\"Discriminator Loss per Epoch\")\naxes[1].set_xlabel(\"Epoch\")\naxes[1].set_ylabel(\"Loss\")\n\naxes[2].plot(history[\"epoch\"], history[\"lr\"], color=\"seagreen\")\naxes[2].set_title(\"Learning Rate Schedule\")\naxes[2].set_xlabel(\"Epoch\")\naxes[2].set_ylabel(\"Learning Rate\")\n\nplt.tight_layout()\nplt.savefig(os.path.join(OUTPUT_DIR, \"training_curves.png\"), dpi=120)\nplt.show()\nprint(f\"Best Generator MAE: {min(history['loss_G']):.4f}\")","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 9. Inference with 8-Way Test Time Augmentation (TTA)","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"generator.load_state_dict(torch.load(ckpt_path, map_location=DEVICE))\ngenerator.eval()\nprint(f\"Loaded best model: {ckpt_path}\")\nprint(\"Running inference with 8-way TTA...\")\n\nto_tensor       = transforms.ToTensor()\nsubmission_data = []\n\nfor img_name in tqdm(sorted(os.listdir(TEST_LR_DIR)), desc=\"Generating SR\"):\n    lr_t = to_tensor(\n        Image.open(os.path.join(TEST_LR_DIR, img_name)).convert(\"RGB\")\n    ).unsqueeze(0).to(DEVICE)\n\n    with torch.no_grad():\n        preds = []\n        for rot in [0, 1, 2, 3]:\n            for flip in [False, True]:\n                aug_t = torch.rot90(lr_t, rot, [2, 3])\n                if flip: aug_t = torch.flip(aug_t, [3])\n                sr_t = generator(aug_t)\n                if flip: sr_t = torch.flip(sr_t, [3])\n                preds.append(torch.rot90(sr_t, -rot, [2, 3]))\n        sr_t = torch.mean(torch.stack(preds), dim=0)\n\n    sr_img = np.round(\n        np.transpose(sr_t.squeeze(0).cpu().clamp(0, 1).numpy(), (1, 2, 0)) * 255\n    ).astype(np.uint8)\n\n    submission_data.append({\n        \"Id\":     img_name,\n        \"Pixels\": \" \".join(sr_img.flatten().astype(str))\n    })\n\nprint(f\"Generated {len(submission_data)} images.\")","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 10. Visual Check of SR Output","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 6, figsize=(18, 6))\nfig.suptitle(\"Inference Results - LR Input vs SR Output\", fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')\n\nsample_names = sorted(os.listdir(TEST_LR_DIR))[:6]\nfor i, fname in enumerate(sample_names):\n    lr_img = Image.open(os.path.join(TEST_LR_DIR, fname))\n    row    = next(r for r in submission_data if r[\"Id\"] == fname)\n    pixels = np.array(list(map(int, row[\"Pixels\"].split())), dtype=np.uint8)\n    sr_img = pixels.reshape(128, 128, 3)\n\n    axes[0, i].imshow(lr_img)\n    axes[0, i].set_title(\"LR 32x32\", fontsize=8)\n    axes[0, i].axis(\"off\")\n\n    axes[1, i].imshow(sr_img)\n    axes[1, i].set_title(\"SR 128x128\", fontsize=8)\n    axes[1, i].axis(\"off\")\n\naxes[0, 0].set_ylabel(\"LR Input\", fontsize=9, fontweight='bold')\naxes[1, 0].set_ylabel(\"SR Output\", fontsize=9, fontweight='bold')\n\nplt.tight_layout()\nplt.savefig(os.path.join(OUTPUT_DIR, \"sr_output_samples.png\"), dpi=120)\nplt.show()","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 11. Build Submission File","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"sub_df   = pd.DataFrame(submission_data).sort_values(\"Id\").reset_index(drop=True)\nsub_path = os.path.join(OUTPUT_DIR, \"submission.csv\")\nsub_df.to_csv(sub_path, index=False)\nprint(f\"submission.csv saved ({os.path.getsize(sub_path)/1e6:.1f} MB)\")\nprint(f\"Shape: {sub_df.shape}\")","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 12. Submission Verification","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"print(\"-\" * 50)\nprint(\"SUBMISSION VERIFICATION\")\nprint(\"-\" * 50)\n\ndf   = pd.read_csv(sub_path)\ncnts = df[\"Pixels\"].apply(lambda s: len(s.split()))\n\nchecks = {\n    \"Row count 495\"       : len(df) == 495,\n    \"Columns correct\"     : list(df.columns) == [\"Id\", \"Pixels\"],\n    \"Pixel count 49152\"   : (cnts == 49152).all(),\n    \"Pixel range [0,255]\" : all(0 <= int(v) <= 255\n                                for v in df[\"Pixels\"].iloc[0].split()[:500]),\n    \"Space delimiter\"     : \",\" not in df[\"Pixels\"].iloc[0],\n    \"Correct ID format\"   : df[\"Id\"].str.startswith(\"agrivision_test_\").all(),\n}\n\nfor check, passed in checks.items():\n    status = \"PASS\" if passed else \"FAIL\"\n    print(f\"[{status}] {check}\")\n\nif all(checks.values()):\n    print(\"\\nAll checks passed. Ready to submit.\")\nelse:\n    print(\"\\nSome checks failed. Review before submitting.\")\n\nprint(f\"\\nPreview:\")\nprint(df[[\"Id\"]].head(3).to_string())","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"---\n\n## Summary: Approaches Tried and Results\n\n### Problem Statement\n\nThe task was to build a Conditional GAN to perform 4x super-resolution on degraded 32x32 crop leaf images and reconstruct 128x128 high-resolution outputs. The evaluation metric is Mean Absolute Error (MAE) computed pixel-by-pixel. The competition baseline is 17.3529644 and a score below this is required to avoid 50% mark deduction.\n\n### Approach 1: UNet Generator with RRDB Bottleneck\n\nThe first approach used a U-Net style encoder-decoder. The encoder progressively upsampled the 32x32 LR input to 128x128 using bilinear interpolation, while Residual-in-Residual Dense Blocks (RRDB) processed features at full 128x128 resolution in the bottleneck. Skip connections from encoder stages were concatenated with decoder outputs.\n\n**Configuration:** Features=64, RRDB=8, L1 + Perceptual loss (VGG19 from dataset), Adam, CosineAnnealingLR, 8-way TTA, batch size=8, normalization to [-1, 1].  \n**Leaderboard MAE:** approximately 16.1\n\n**Observations:**\n- Stable training with val MAE improving from 17.5 at epoch 1 to 16.8 by epoch 120.\n- The gap between validation MAE and leaderboard score was consistently around 0.7.\n- Adding a GAN discriminator without warmup caused the leaderboard score to worsen to 18.7 due to training instability.\n- Normalization to [-1, 1] with Tanh output caused incorrect inference results in some configurations, producing 18.7-18.8 leaderboard scores despite good training MAE.\n\n### Approach 2: RCAB Generator with PixelShuffle (Final Approach)\n\nThe second approach processes features at the LR resolution (32x32) using Residual Channel Attention Blocks (RCAB), then upsamples using two sequential PixelShuffle x2 operations to reach 128x128. A global bicubic residual connection adds the bicubic upscaled LR image to the model output.\n\n**Configuration:** Features=96, 16 RCAB blocks, residual scaling=0.1, Charbonnier loss + Perceptual loss (VGG19 from dataset) + GAN adversarial loss, AdamW with weight decay, CosineAnnealingWarmRestarts, 8-way TTA, raw [0,1] pixel values (no normalization), batch size=16.  \n**Leaderboard MAE:** 15.9 (best result)\n\n**Observations:**\n- Using raw [0,1] pixel values without normalization was critical. Previous [-1,1] normalization caused inference bugs.\n- The 8-way TTA using torch.rot90 directly on tensors was more reliable than PIL rotation-based TTA.\n- Processing at LR resolution (32x32) made training approximately 10x faster than processing at HR resolution.\n- Residual scaling (res_scale=0.1) prevented gradient explosion during training.\n- Gradient clipping (max_norm=1.0) further stabilized training.\n- The Charbonnier loss (smooth L1 variant) performed slightly better than plain L1 for this task.\n\n### What Worked\n\n- Raw [0,1] pixel values with no normalization\n- 8-way TTA using torch.rot90 on tensors\n- Charbonnier loss as the primary training objective\n- AdamW with weight decay=1e-4 for regularization\n- CosineAnnealingWarmRestarts for learning rate scheduling\n- Residual scaling (res_scale=0.1) inside RCAB blocks\n- Global bicubic residual connection in the generator\n- Gradient clipping (max_norm=1.0)\n- VGG19 perceptual loss loaded from the provided dataset file\n\n### What Did Not Work\n\n- [-1,1] normalization with Tanh output activation\n- GAN training without warmup (destabilized early training)\n- Warmup learning rate scheduling\n- Frequency loss combined with high perceptual loss weight\n- PixelShuffle trained on full data for 500 epochs without a validation split (severe overfitting)\n\n### Rule Compliance\n\n- Generator and Discriminator are randomly initialized. No pretrained weights used for the core task.\n- VGG19 weights are loaded only from the provided `vgg19_weights.pth` file in the competition dataset, used only for perceptual loss computation.\n- The notebook runs with Internet Access OFF and External Data DISALLOWED.\n- Submission format follows the competition specification: space-separated pixel values, 49152 integers per row, [0,255] range.\n\n### Final Result\n\n**Architecture:** Conditional GAN — RCAB Generator + Conditional Discriminator  \n**Training:** 150 epochs, AdamW, CosineAnnealingWarmRestarts, Charbonnier + Perceptual + Adversarial loss  \n**Inference:** 8-way Test Time Augmentation  \n**Leaderboard MAE:** 15.9 (below baseline of 17.3529)","metadata":{}}]}